15/06/2006
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Slovenia will seal a bilateral agreement on defence co-operation by the end of this year, according to an announcement Wednesday (14 June), during BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic's first official visit to Ljubljana.
Slovenian counterpart Karel Erjavec reaffirmed his country's support for BiH's Euro-Atlantic integration aspirations, saying the Western Balkans are viewed as a priority.
(Slovenian Government Web site, RTRS, Beta - 14/06/06)
